</taxonomicName>
: 16 — innerets of male; 17–18 bulb, ventral and anterior, embolus is broken; 19 — epigyne, dorsal; 20 — right part of epigyne, antero-dorsal; 21 — tibia and cymbium of male palp, retrolateral; 22 — epiandrous region; 23 — male abdomen, ventral. Scale = 0.1 mm if not otherwise indicated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9736B8FFA9FFEFE8CE27CDFD5FF9FE" blockId="3.[174,1233,1365,1547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">
Abbreviations: 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFE90527CDFE80FA20" box="[357,382,1472,1493]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Ar</emphasis>
— accessorial receptacle, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEA1D27CCFD6AFA23" box="[637,660,1473,1494]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Bc</emphasis>
