<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEB0327CDFC80FA20" box="[867,894,1472,1493]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Cd</emphasis>
— copulatory duct, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEC2A27CDFB9EFA20" box="[1098,1120,1472,1493]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Cf</emphasis>
— cymbial fold, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFE8BF27D6FF0AFA05" box="[223,244,1499,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Cl</emphasis>
— colulus, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFE90827D6FE7DFA05" box="[360,387,1499,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Co</emphasis>
— conductor, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEA7527D6FDD0FA05" box="[533,558,1499,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Ea</emphasis>
— epiandrus, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEADC27D6FD22FA05" box="[700,732,1499,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Em</emphasis>
— embolus, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEB3D27D6FC8BFA05" box="[861,885,1499,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Re</emphasis>
— receptacle, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEC6327D6FBE5FA05" box="[1027,1051,1499,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Rg</emphasis>
— gland of receptacle, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFE88527FBFF05F9FE" box="[229,251,1526,1547]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Rs</emphasis>
— round swelling, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFE9D727FBFE2FF9FE" box="[439,465,1526,1547]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Ta</emphasis>
— tegular apophysis.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9736B8FFA9FFEFE8832438FDC1F905" blockId="3.[174,1232,1589,1840]" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">
Palp as in 
<figureCitation id="13132A3DFFA9FFEFE9382438FE4FF9A5" box="[344,433,1589,1616]" captionStart="Figs 1‒7" captionStartId="1.[170,209,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[235,1164,612,1730]" captionTargetId="figure-137@1.[235,1164,612,1730]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1‒7. Habitus and male palp of Argistes velox: 1–2 — female habitus, lateral and dorsal; 3 — male habitus, lateral; 4‒5 — male palp, retro- and prolateral; 6‒7 — prosoma frontal in female and male. Scale = 0.2 mm if not otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449352/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">figs 4‒5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13132A3DFFA9FFEFE9DB2438FE0AF9A5" box="[443,500,1589,1616]" captionStart="Figs 8‒15" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[238,1132,787,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-221@2.[238,1132,786,1657]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 8‒15. Copulatory organs and abdomen of Argistes velox: 8–10 — male palp, ventral, ventro-prolateral and dorsal; 11–12 — ventral side of abdomen in female and male; 13 — intact epigyne, ventral; 14–15 — macerated epigyne, ventral and dorsal. Scale = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Ar — accessorial receptacle, Bc — bursa copulatrix, Cd — copulatory duct, Co conductor, Ea — epiandrus, Em — embolus, Mp — median pocket, Re — receptacle, Rg — gland of receptacle, Ta — tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449354" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449354/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">8‒10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13132A3DFFA9FFEFE99E2438FD90F9A5" box="[510,622,1589,1616]" captionStart="Figs 16–23" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1365,1387]" captionTargetBox="[234,1183,174,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-124@3.[234,1183,174,1317]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 16–23. Somatic characters and copulatory organs of Argistes velox: 16 — innerets of male; 17–18 bulb, ventral and anterior, embolus is broken; 19 — epigyne, dorsal; 20 — right part of epigyne, antero-dorsal; 21 — tibia and cymbium of male palp, retrolateral; 22 — epiandrous region; 23 — male abdomen, ventral. Scale = 0.1 mm if not otherwise indicated. Abbreviations: Ar — accessorial receptacle, Bc — bursa copulatrix, Cd — copulatory duct, Cf — cymbial fold, Cl — colulus, Co — conductor, Ea — epiandrus, Em — embolus, Re — receptacle, Rg — gland of receptacle, Rs — round swelling, Ta — tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449356/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">17‒18, 21</figureCitation>
: long, longer than carapace; femur equal in length to patella + tibia; tibia 3 times longer than wide, with short, slightly bent retrolateral apophysis; cymbium long, with long apical part and basal fold (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEB282478FC9DF97A" box="[840,867,1653,1679]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Cf</emphasis>
); bulb oval, with long straight, not hooked, tegular apophysis (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEA7C2498FDC2F95B" box="[540,572,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Ta</emphasis>
); spermophore with characteristic loops (
<figureCitation id="13132A3DFFA9FFEFEC7F2498FBA4F945" box="[1055,1114,1685,1712]" captionStart="Figs 8‒15" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[238,1132,787,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-221@2.[238,1132,786,1657]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 8‒15. Copulatory organs and abdomen of Argistes velox: 8–10 — male palp, ventral, ventro-prolateral and dorsal; 11–12 — ventral side of abdomen in female and male; 13 — intact epigyne, ventral; 14–15 — macerated epigyne, ventral and dorsal. Scale = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Ar — accessorial receptacle, Bc — bursa copulatrix, Cd — copulatory duct, Co conductor, Ea — epiandrus, Em — embolus, Mp — median pocket, Re — receptacle, Rg — gland of receptacle, Ta — tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449354" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449354/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">fig. 9</figureCitation>
); conductor (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFE88224B8FEFCF93A" box="[226,258,1717,1743]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Co</emphasis>
) weakly sclerotized, with widened tip; embolus (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFA9FFEFEB2124B8FC96F93B" box="[833,872,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">Em</emphasis>
) claw-like. Length of palp and relative length of cymbial tip vary.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9736B8FFA9FFE8E88324F8FD32FEDF" blockId="3.[174,1232,1589,1840]" lastBlockId="4.[166,1225,175,394]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="367" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">
Female. Total length 3.5 (variation 3.4‒3.5). Carapace 1.8 long, 1.14 wide. Colouration as in male (
<figureCitation id="13132A3DFFA9FFEFE95A2518FE66F8C5" box="[314,408,1813,1840]" captionStart="Figs 1‒7" captionStartId="1.[170,209,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[235,1164,612,1730]" captionTargetId="figure-137@1.[235,1164,612,1730]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs 1‒7. Habitus and male palp of Argistes velox: 1–2 — female habitus, lateral and dorsal; 3 — male habitus, lateral; 4‒5 — male palp, retro- and prolateral; 6‒7 — prosoma frontal in female and male. Scale = 0.2 mm if not otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449352/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">figs 1‒2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13132A3DFFA9FFEFE9C62518FE3BF8C5" box="[422,453,1813,1840]" captionStart="Figs 8‒15" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[238,1132,787,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-221@2.[238,1132,786,1657]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 8‒15. Copulatory organs and abdomen of Argistes velox: 8–10 — male palp, ventral, ventro-prolateral and dorsal; 11–12 — ventral side of abdomen in female and male; 13 — intact epigyne, ventral; 14–15 — macerated epigyne, ventral and dorsal. Scale = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Ar — accessorial receptacle, Bc — bursa copulatrix, Cd — copulatory duct, Co conductor, Ea — epiandrus, Em — embolus, Mp — median pocket, Re — receptacle, Rg — gland of receptacle, Ta — tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449354" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449354/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="366">11</figureCitation>
). Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.14, AME-AME 0.04, PME 0.09, PME-PME 0.11. Spination differs on left and right legs and in different specimens. Femora: II 1d, III 3d, IV 2d; tibia III 1p, 2r, 1–1v, IV 5p, 2r, 2–2v and 1–1va; metatarsi: II 1–1v, III 3p 3r, 1–1v, IV 3r, 2–2v, 1–1va. Legs I–II thinner than III–IV, middle part of femur I 
<quantity id="4CD09B5DFFAEFFE8E9652302FEABFEDF" box="[261,341,271,298]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" unit="in" value="0.17">0.17 in</quantity>
diameter and femur IV — 0.27.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9736B8FFAEFFE9E8BB2322FF1AFEFF" blockId="4.[166,1225,175,394]" lastBlockId="5.[174,1233,175,330]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="368" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
Epigyne as in 
<figureCitation id="13132A3DFFAEFFE8E91F2322FDE0FEBF" box="[383,542,303,330]" captionStart="Figs 8‒15" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1687,1709]" captionTargetBox="[238,1132,787,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-221@2.[238,1132,786,1657]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 8‒15. Copulatory organs and abdomen of Argistes velox: 8–10 — male palp, ventral, ventro-prolateral and dorsal; 11–12 — ventral side of abdomen in female and male; 13 — intact epigyne, ventral; 14–15 — macerated epigyne, ventral and dorsal. Scale = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Ar — accessorial receptacle, Bc — bursa copulatrix, Cd — copulatory duct, Co conductor, Ea — epiandrus, Em — embolus, Mp — median pocket, Re — receptacle, Rg — gland of receptacle, Ta — tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449354" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449354/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">figs 11, 13‒15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13132A3DFFAEFFE8EA4A2322FD8CFEBF" box="[554,626,303,330]" captionStart="Figs 16–23" captionStartId="3.[174,213,1365,1387]" captionTargetBox="[234,1183,174,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-124@3.[234,1183,174,1317]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 16–23. Somatic characters and copulatory organs of Argistes velox: 16 — innerets of male; 17–18 bulb, ventral and anterior, embolus is broken; 19 — epigyne, dorsal; 20 — right part of epigyne, antero-dorsal; 21 — tibia and cymbium of male palp, retrolateral; 22 — epiandrous region; 23 — male abdomen, ventral. Scale = 0.1 mm if not otherwise indicated. Abbreviations: Ar — accessorial receptacle, Bc — bursa copulatrix, Cd — copulatory duct, Cf — cymbial fold, Cl — colulus, Co — conductor, Ea — epiandrus, Em — embolus, Re — receptacle, Rg — gland of receptacle, Rs — round swelling, Ta — tegular apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449356/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">19‒20</figureCitation>
: plate with small median pocket (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFAEFFE8EB9B233DFBDDFEBC" box="[1019,1059,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Mp</emphasis>
) faced anteriorly, copulatory openings (bursa copulatrix, 
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFAEFFE8EAD1235DFD33FE9C" box="[689,717,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Bc</emphasis>
) round, spaced by 4 diameters; translucent receptacles (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFAEFFE8E95A237DFEA9FE7C" box="[314,343,368,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Re</emphasis>
) spaced by 1.5 diameters; receptacles kidney-shaped, with weakly sclero- tized glands (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFAFFFE9E92922BDFE99FF3C" box="[329,359,176,201]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">Rg</emphasis>
) latero-anteriorly; copulatory ducts (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFAFFFE9EB7822A2FCC4FF3C" box="[792,826,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">Cd</emphasis>
) broad, as long as receptacles, with a kind of small and globular “accessorial” receptacle (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFAFFFE9EB4B22DDFCB7FF1F" box="[811,841,208,234]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">Ar</emphasis>
) originated from round swelling (
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFAFFFE9E8D822FDFF2DFEFC" box="[184,211,240,265]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">Rs</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF576630FFAEFFE8E8CA24FCFED8F8D7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449360" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6449360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449360/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" startId="4.[170,203,1777,1799]" targetBox="[219,1126,457,1748]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8B9736B8FFAEFFE8E8CA24FCFED8F8D7" blockId="4.[170,1210,1777,1826]" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">
Fig. 24. Distribution records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284D3BFFAEFFE8E9BF24FFFD9CF8F3" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1897" box="[479,610,1777,1799]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Argistes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="velox">
<emphasis id="B95CEAAAFFAEFFE8E9BF24FFFD9CF8F3" box="[479,610,1777,1799]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Argistes velox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Filled circles refer to literature data and open circles refer to present data.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9736B8FFAFFFE9E8832302FC85FEBF" blockId="5.[174,1233,175,330]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
N o t e. Males examined are smaller in size than those described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB94B49FFAFFFE9EB822302FF00FEBF" author="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L." pageId="5" pageNumber="368" pagination="1 - 591" refId="ref1785" refString="Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L. 2001. Forest spiders of South East Asia: with a revision of the sac and ground spiders (Araneae: Clubionidae, Corinnidae, Liocranidae, Gnaphosidae, Prodidomidae and Trochanterriidae). Brill, Leiden, 1 - 591." type="book chapter" year="2001">Deeleman-Reinhold (2001)</bibRefCitation>
: 2.5‒2.85 vs. 3.0, but have longer legs (leg I 7.0 vs. 6.0).
</paragraph>
